{
  "slug": "saori-free-form-weaving",
  "title": "SAORI free-form weaving",
  "subtitle": "Intuitive weaving without a fixed structure or draft",
  "excerpt": "SAORI is a Japanese weaving philosophy founded in 1969 that removes all rules about pattern, sett, and technique. Each piece is woven as direct self-expression in thread. It is an excellent starting point for complete beginners because there are no requirements to meet.",
  "type": "TECHNIQUE",
  "categorySlug": "fibre-arts",
  "subCategorySlug": "weaving",
  "difficulty": "BEGINNER",
  "season": null,
  "sourceType": "PUBLIC_DOMAIN",
  "sourceNotes": "- SAORI as a philosophy was founded by Misao Jo, Japan, 1969. The name 'SAORI' is trademarked by the SAORI organisation for workshop certification; the weaving method and philosophy are freely describable. No source quotation used.\n- General frame-loom setup from public domain textile references.",
